{"author":{"id":"daecaa79b752289d08fa06c7a65c8d0387caf00b7e262b5741f4805727d0a582"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1592386761,"nonce":"DZIO9gIQpTy9FjjXvt3SdUr3/CQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU2NDAyOTY2Mjg=","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/406","origin":"github"},"title":"Bridge credentials should be read from the full configuration chain","message":"`git-bug` does not currently read bridge configuration from anything except the user configuration file, e.g. `${HOME}/.gitconfig`. It would be awesome if the full configuration chain could be supported, in order of precedence:\n\n- Local configuration -- `${REPO_ROOT}/.git/config`\n- User configuration -- `${HOME}/.gitconfig` or `${XDG_CONFIG_HOME}/git/config`\n- System configuration -- `/etc/gitconfig`\n\nAdditionally, following `include` directives would be useful -- the main application for which is likely keeping the authentication configuration out of the default user-scoped conffile which is stored in a repository for public sharing.","files":null}]}